            <p>A low-cost airline is a budget airline or a discounted airline for travel goals that operate on the minimum cost. The operation cost is relatively low for this airline in comparison to other airlines with low-cost flag carriers, and that's why these are the most affordable airlines with which to book tickets. Airlines that come under the category of low-cost airlines offer the cheapest airfare in comparison to luxury airlines but charge extra on other travel fees such as carry-on baggage. Low-cost is a term that is defined on the base of operating cost structure rather than their competitor's airlines. The low-cost airline offers low-ticket prices with limited services because they are working on the low-cost model. Most of the low-cost airlines operate short-haul flights and offer the lowest airfare. </p>
