            <p>You can get Point-to-Point flights from these flag carriers. These airlines provide direct flights to regional or secondary airports and reduce the travel time for the routes. That means, for short-distance flights, these flag carriers are the right choice for the passengers. </p>
            <h3>Frequent promotions</h3>
            <p>The low-cost airline offers the best deals and frequent promotions on air tickets. Take advantage of the deals, discounts, and flash sales to secure the best price. The best thing is that you will pay for the services that you use during the travel, and you can avoid unnecessary expenses such as meals, seat selection, or checked baggage. </p>
            <h3>Expanded Route Networks</h3>
            <p>There are many budget airlines right now offering expanded international and domestic routes for long-haul travel. Thus, if you think that only short-haul flights are available with low-cost airlines, then you are wrong. </p>
